WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:06.745
PICK A CARD.
ANY CARD.

00:06.832 --> 00:08.660
WHAT DOES THIS HAVE TO DO
WITH OUR PROPERTY-FRAUD SCAM?

00:08.747 --> 00:09.748
YOU'LL HAVE
THE WHOLE THING CRACKED

00:09.835 --> 00:10.749
BEFORE I CAN SAY "TA-DA."

00:10.836 --> 00:12.012
PICK A DEED.
[ SIGHS ]

00:13.100 --> 00:14.101
NOW WHAT?

00:14.188 --> 00:16.059
NOW I TAKE
THESE 51 DEEDS

00:16.146 --> 00:17.626
AND FIGURE OUT
WHICH ONE YOU TOOK.

00:17.713 --> 00:19.019
IT'S NOT MAGIC.
IT'S MATH.

00:19.106 --> 00:20.411
WE GO THROUGH
THE TITLE COMPANY'S RECORDS,

00:20.498 --> 00:21.499
MATCH THEM
WITH THE REALTOR'S,

00:21.586 --> 00:22.674
AND FIGURE OUT
WHICH ONE IS MISSING.

00:22.761 --> 00:23.675
TA-DA.

00:23.762 --> 00:25.112
NICE WORK.

00:25.199 --> 00:27.201
BUT HERE'S ANOTHER CASE
WE NEED TO MAKE DISAPPEAR.

00:27.288 --> 00:29.159
SELENA THOMAS.
MM.

00:29.246 --> 00:30.030
WHO'S SHE?

00:30.117 --> 00:31.857
DEVOTED SERIAL MONOGAMIST

00:31.944 --> 00:34.077
WHO MARRIES WEALTHY MEN
RIGHT BEFORE THEY DIE.

00:34.164 --> 00:35.078
A BLACK WIDOW.

00:35.165 --> 00:36.514
COULD BE.

00:36.601 --> 00:38.125
SHE HAS FOUR
RICH LATE HUSBANDS.

00:38.212 --> 00:39.735
SHE GETS AROUND.

00:39.822 --> 00:41.954
AND NOW SHE'S FINALLY
GETTING AROUND TO NEW YORK.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.695
QUITE THE QUEEN
OF HEARTS.

00:43.782 --> 00:44.740
CUTE.

00:44.827 --> 00:45.784
YOU LIKE THAT?

00:45.871 --> 00:47.047
MOVE IT, COPPERFIELD.

00:47.134 --> 00:48.744
THEIR DEATHS ARE LISTED
AS NATURAL --

00:48.831 --> 00:49.875
HEART ATTACK, EMBOLISM,

00:49.962 --> 00:51.747
SKYDIVING ACCIDENT.

00:51.834 --> 00:53.444
WHAT ABOUT THE FOURTH GUY?

00:53.531 --> 00:55.794
WE'RE WAITING ON THE L.A. BUREAU
TO SEND THEIR REPORT.

00:55.881 --> 00:57.709
FOUR HUSBANDS,
FOUR DEAD BODIES.

00:57.796 --> 01:00.364
WE THINK SHE'S KILLING THEM,
BUT WE DON'T KNOW WHY.

01:00.451 --> 01:02.192
THEY'RE NOT LEAVING HER
ALL THEIR MONEY?

01:02.279 --> 01:03.846
NOPE.
THAT'S WHAT YOU'D EXPECT.

01:03.933 --> 01:05.848
BUT SHE'S NOT COLLECTING ON
ANY OF THE INSURANCE PAYOFFS.

01:05.935 --> 01:07.458
WE FLAGGED HER NAME ON THIS.

01:07.545 --> 01:09.112
IT'S AN APPLICATION

01:09.199 --> 01:12.420
FOR THE MANHATTAN MILLIONAIRE
SOCIETY BACHELORS AUCTION.

01:12.507 --> 01:15.249
IF SHE'S GONNA BE AT
THIS AUCTION, THEN SO ARE WE.

01:15.336 --> 01:17.729
CLUB HAS THREE OPEN SLOTS
FOR ELIGIBLE MEN.

01:17.816 --> 01:19.688
THAT MEANS I NEED
THREE VOLUNTEERS.

01:19.775 --> 01:21.124
NEAL, RAISE YOUR HAND.

01:21.211 --> 01:23.474
DO I HAVE TO?
YES.

01:23.561 --> 01:25.868
THERE'S OUR FIRST
LUCKY BACHELOR.

01:25.955 --> 01:27.609
COME ON.

01:27.696 --> 01:30.438
WE'LL CREATE VERY IRRESISTIBLE
IDENTITIES FOR YOU GUYS.

01:30.525 --> 01:32.527
YEAH, THEN HOPE SHE DOESN'T
KILL HER LATEST BOY TOY

01:32.614 --> 01:33.615
BEFORE WE FIND THE MONEY.

01:33.702 --> 01:34.659
THAT'S A HAND.

01:34.746 --> 01:35.834
JONES IS NUMBER TWO.

01:35.921 --> 01:37.532
NO, PETER, I DIDN'T --ONE MORE.

01:37.619 --> 01:38.924
COME ON.
IT'S ONLY A COVER.

01:39.011 --> 01:40.143
WHO'S NUMBER THREE?

01:40.230 --> 01:42.363
HOW ABOUT YOU,PETER?

01:42.450 --> 01:44.060
I MEAN, YOU SEEM LIKE
THE MARRYING KIND, RIGHT?

01:44.147 --> 01:45.670
I AMMARRIED.

01:45.757 --> 01:47.150
HEY...
IT'S ONLY A COVER.

01:47.237 --> 01:49.021
BE NICE TO GIVE HER
SOME VARIETY.

01:49.109 --> 01:50.414
UNLESS --
GUYS, GUYS,

01:50.501 --> 01:51.459
UNLESS, YOU KNOW,
YOU NEED PERMISSION.

01:51.546 --> 01:52.503
[ ALL MURMURING ]

01:52.590 --> 01:54.505
I DON'T -- I DON'T --
NO, I --

01:54.592 --> 01:56.768
O-OKAY, FINE.
I'LL DO IT.

01:56.855 --> 01:57.813
ALL RIGHT.

01:57.900 --> 01:58.814
LET'S SET IT UP.

02:01.512 --> 02:02.948
ARE YOU SCARED
TO TELL ELIZABETH?

02:03.035 --> 02:04.776
TERRIFIED.

02:10.347 --> 02:11.957
MY ROLE IN
THE ASSIGNMENT'S MINIMAL.

02:12.044 --> 02:13.220
[ SIGHS ] RIGHT.

02:13.307 --> 02:14.786
YOU'RE PLAYING
PIECE OF MEAT NUMBER 2.

02:14.873 --> 02:16.048
YOU'RE GONNA FLIRT --

02:16.136 --> 02:17.789
TALK.
I'M GONNA TALKTO THEM.

02:17.876 --> 02:19.617
AND THEN YOU'RE GONNA WALK
ACROSS A STAGE

02:19.704 --> 02:21.228
WHILE THESE WOMEN
ARE BIDDING ON YOU.

02:21.315 --> 02:23.143
EL, MY CHANCES
OF BEING PICKED

02:23.230 --> 02:24.622
ARE SLIM TO NONE
BETWEEN NEAL AND --

02:24.709 --> 02:25.884
WAIT. HOLD ON.

02:25.971 --> 02:27.538
YOUR CHANCES
ARE NOTSLIM.

02:27.625 --> 02:29.236
HONEY, LOOK AT YOU.

02:29.323 --> 02:31.586
I'M HOLDING POOP.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.283
AND YOU LOOK DAMN SEXY
DOING IT.

02:33.370 --> 02:34.589
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHAT?

02:34.676 --> 02:35.981
YOU'RE GONNA WIN
THIS THING.

02:36.068 --> 02:37.069
I AM?
YEAH.

02:37.157 --> 02:38.288
I'M GONNA
MAKE SURE OF IT.

02:38.375 --> 02:40.856
COME ON.

02:40.943 --> 02:42.640
WHAT'S THE GRAND PRIZE
ON THIS?

02:42.727 --> 02:44.338
I GET TO TAKE
A VERY LOVELY,

02:44.425 --> 02:46.340
VERY DANGEROUS WOMAN
OUT ON A DATE.

02:46.427 --> 02:49.038
HMM. IT'S NOTHING
YOU CAN'T HANDLE.

02:49.125 --> 02:50.822
THANKS TO YOU.

02:50.909 --> 02:53.521
UH, WE,ACTUALLY,
HAVE NEVER BEEN ON A DATE.

02:53.608 --> 02:55.131
PETER AND ELIZABETH'S
HOUSE.

02:55.218 --> 02:56.524
DINNER DATE.
NOT DATEDATE.

02:56.611 --> 02:57.481
DEFINE "DATEDATE."

02:57.568 --> 02:58.526
ONE-ON-ONE.

02:58.613 --> 02:59.527
WHAT ABOUT LUNCHES?

02:59.614 --> 03:00.832
LUNCH IS NOT ROMANTIC.

03:00.919 --> 03:02.051
LUNCH IS LUNCH.

03:02.138 --> 03:04.401
WE'VE NEVER BEEN
ON A REAL DATE.

03:04.488 --> 03:06.795
IT'S OKAY.
WHAT'S YOUR COVER?

03:06.882 --> 03:08.840
PLAYBOY SON
OF A TEXAS OIL TYCOON.

03:08.927 --> 03:10.190
OH, WELL!

03:10.277 --> 03:11.321
I LIKE THE ACCENT.

03:11.408 --> 03:13.454
I'M GLAD YOU DO, MA'AM.[ LAUGHS ]

03:13.541 --> 03:15.673
THERE'S GONNA BE
A VERY BIGPROBLEM, THOUGH.

03:15.760 --> 03:17.197
WHAT'S THAT?

03:17.284 --> 03:18.894
ALL THE WOMEN
ARE GONNA WANT YOU,

03:18.981 --> 03:20.809
SO WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN YOUR KILLER GETS OUTBID?

03:20.896 --> 03:23.246
I SEE YOUR POINT.
MM-HMM.

03:23.333 --> 03:25.248
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO THROW
YOUR MEETINGS

03:25.335 --> 03:26.728
WITH ALL
THE OTHER WOMEN.

03:26.815 --> 03:27.903
HOW DO I DO THAT?

03:27.990 --> 03:29.774
WELL, WE ARE VERYSHALLOW CREATURES,

03:29.861 --> 03:32.951
BUT THERE ARE THINGS THAT EVEN
BEAUTIFUL MEN LIKE YOU DO

03:33.038 --> 03:34.997
THAT DRIVE US NUTS.

03:35.084 --> 03:37.042
OH, YOU'RE GOOD.

03:37.129 --> 03:39.393
ALL RIGHT, HONEY,
LET'S GO OVER THIS AGAIN.

03:39.480 --> 03:40.524
YOU ARE...

03:40.611 --> 03:42.439
PETER WILLIAMS,
U.S. STEEL MAGNATE.

03:42.526 --> 03:45.094
MM. AND TELL ME MORE
ABOUT THE STEEL INDUSTRY.

03:45.181 --> 03:47.314
WELL, IT BEGAN
AS A FAMILY BUSINESS.

03:47.401 --> 03:48.663
BORING, BORING, BORING.BY THEN --

03:48.750 --> 03:49.664
WHAT DID WE DISCUSS?

03:49.751 --> 03:51.231
RIGHT.

03:51.318 --> 03:54.234
UH, YOU DON'T WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT WHAT I DO.

03:54.321 --> 03:56.845
I REALLY WANT TO KNOW MORE
ABOUT YOU.

03:56.932 --> 03:58.847
MM. AND WHY ARE YOU
STILL SINGLE?

03:58.934 --> 04:00.327
HAVEN'T FOUND
THE RIGHT WOMAN YET.

04:00.414 --> 04:02.198
MM. WHO MIGHT
THIS RIGHT WOMAN BE?

04:02.285 --> 04:05.201
OH, WELL,
SHE'S ABOUT 5'5",

04:05.288 --> 04:07.551
BRUNETTE, MOST BEAUTIFUL
BLUE EYES I'VE EVER SEEN,

04:07.638 --> 04:08.683
SMART AS A WHIP,

04:08.770 --> 04:09.727
AND GORGEOUS AS HELL.

04:09.814 --> 04:11.903
AWW. PERFECT.

04:11.990 --> 04:13.644
OKAY. REMEMBER,
THIS IS A CONVERSATION,

04:13.731 --> 04:15.080
NOT AN INTERROGATION,

04:15.167 --> 04:16.952
SO YOU GOT TO MOVE AWAY
FROM THE "WHERE ARE YOU FROMs"

04:17.039 --> 04:18.083
AND "WHAT DO YOU DOs,"

04:18.170 --> 04:19.041
AND, HONEY,
DON'T MAKE THAT FACE.

04:19.128 --> 04:20.695
WHAT FACE? THATFACE.

04:20.782 --> 04:22.044
OH.
RIGHT. YES.

04:22.131 --> 04:24.829
BE YOURSELF.
YOU'RE GONNA BE GREAT.

04:24.916 --> 04:25.874
OKAY.

04:25.961 --> 04:26.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:26.962 --> 04:27.876
THANKS, HON.

04:27.963 --> 04:29.051
BYE.
SEE YA.

04:36.145 --> 04:37.277
OH.

04:37.364 --> 04:38.626
HAVE WE, UH, MET?

04:38.713 --> 04:39.757
I DON'T BELIEVE WE HAVE.

04:39.844 --> 04:41.019
ARTHUR FORT, PASTRY BARON

04:41.106 --> 04:42.847
TO A MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR
DESSERT EMPIRE.

04:42.934 --> 04:44.327
LADIES LOVE THE SWEETS.

04:44.414 --> 04:46.024
Neal: YOU READY?
ARE YOU?

04:46.111 --> 04:48.200
GENTLEMEN,
WE ARE ABOUT TO BEGIN.

04:48.288 --> 04:49.419
I WILL MAKE THE ANNOUNCEMENT,

04:49.506 --> 04:51.639
AND WHEN I GIVE YOU
THE GO-AHEAD,

04:51.726 --> 04:54.119
YOU JUST TAKE YOUR PLACES
ON THE STAIRS, OKAY?

04:54.206 --> 04:57.209
GOOD LUCK.

04:57.297 --> 05:01.388
OKAY, LADIES, I HAVE ONLY
ONE QUESTION FOR YOU!

05:01.475 --> 05:05.000
ARE YOU READY TO MEET
YOUR MEN?

05:05.087 --> 05:08.960
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

05:11.441 --> 05:13.269
[ WHISTLING, WOMEN
CHANTING "MEN! MEN! MEN!" ]

05:13.356 --> 05:15.010
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:15.097 --> 05:16.838
WHY DO I FEEL LIKE
I NEED A PIKE AND SWORD?

05:16.925 --> 05:19.667
FOR THOSE ABOUT TO DATE...

05:19.754 --> 05:21.277
WE SALUTE YOU.

05:40.035 --> 05:44.256
OKAY, LADIES, YOU'LL HAVE FIVE
MINUTES TO TALK TO EACH MAN.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.606
WHEN THE BELL SOUNDS...[ BELL TINKLES ]

05:45.693 --> 05:48.217
...YOU SIMPLY MOVE ON
TO THE NEXT.

05:48.304 --> 05:49.436
NOW, WHY DON'T YOU GO AHEAD
AND CHECK YOUR INVITATIONS

05:49.523 --> 05:50.698
FOR THE PROPER ROTATION.

05:50.785 --> 05:53.440
YOU EVER DONE ANYTHING
LIKE THIS BEFORE?

05:55.137 --> 05:56.443
YES.

05:56.530 --> 05:58.401
WHAT DO YOULOOK FOR?

05:58.488 --> 06:01.926
MM. TALL, DARK, AND HANDSOME
IS FINE WITH ME.

06:02.013 --> 06:04.625
YOU CAN ALSO TELL A LOT
ABOUT A MAN BY HIS SMILE,

06:04.712 --> 06:06.801
HOW CONFIDENT
OR COUNTERFEIT HE CAN BE.

06:06.888 --> 06:09.281
MM.SO WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

06:09.369 --> 06:11.327
I'M GONNA BOMB EVERY MEETING
EXCEPT SELENA.

06:11.414 --> 06:13.198
MM. YOU'RE AFRAID
YOU'LL CAUSE A FRENZY.

06:13.285 --> 06:14.809
I'M NARROWING THE ODDS.

06:14.896 --> 06:16.332
WHAT'S YOUR APPROACH?

06:16.419 --> 06:18.160
I'M GOING FOR THE FRENZY.MM.

06:18.247 --> 06:20.380
I'M GONNA TRY TO CHARM
EVERY ONE OF THEM.

06:20.467 --> 06:21.685
I WANT GOOD WORD OF MOUTH.

06:21.772 --> 06:22.991
SURE.

06:23.078 --> 06:24.340
PETER.

06:24.427 --> 06:26.255
I'M GONNA MAINTAIN
EYE CONTACT

06:26.342 --> 06:28.126
AND REMEMBER
IT'S A CONVERSATION,

06:28.213 --> 06:29.345
NOT AN INTERROGATION.

06:29.432 --> 06:31.129
THAT'S ALL GOOD,

06:31.216 --> 06:32.435
BUT WHAT YOU WANT TO DO,
YOU WANT TO KEEP IT UP HERE

06:32.522 --> 06:33.741
WHEN YOU TALK, RIGHT?

06:33.828 --> 06:35.960
DOWN HERE, THIS IS ALL
SECOND-DATE TERRITORY.

06:36.047 --> 06:37.092
OKAY, SO BE YOURSELF.

06:37.179 --> 06:38.572
JUST BE YOURSELF UP HERE.

06:38.659 --> 06:40.356
AND IF YOU'RE HOLDING A DRINK,
KEEP IT IN YOUR LEFT HAND.

06:40.443 --> 06:41.749
THAT WAY, WHEN YOU SHAKE
HER HAND WITH YOUR RIGHT,

06:41.836 --> 06:42.532
YOUR FIRST TOUCH
WON'T BE COLD.

06:45.796 --> 06:48.103
YEAH, IT ISCOLD.

06:48.190 --> 06:49.757
Jameson:
ONE FINAL REMINDER --

06:49.844 --> 06:52.499
SOME OF THE MEN
HAVE BEEN KNOWN TO PROPOSE

06:52.586 --> 06:54.762
ON THE VERY NIGHT
OF THE AUCTION,

06:54.849 --> 06:56.981
SO, PLEASE, DON'T FORGET
TO CHECK THEIR POCKETS

06:57.068 --> 06:57.982
FOR ENGAGEMENT RINGS.

06:58.069 --> 07:01.682
OKAY, MILLIONAIRES,

07:01.769 --> 07:04.467
THE MOMENT ALL THESE BEAUTIFUL
LADIES HAVE BEEN WAITING FOR.

07:04.554 --> 07:08.340
ON YOUR MARKS, GET SET...

07:08.428 --> 07:09.603
DATE!

07:09.690 --> 07:12.649
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

07:12.736 --> 07:15.043
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:15.130 --> 07:17.045
HI. WHERE WERE YOU
BEFORE NEW YORK?

07:17.132 --> 07:18.481
CLEVELAND.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:18.568 --> 07:20.701
FASCINATING.

07:20.788 --> 07:24.052
TELL ME MORE
ABOUT CLEVELAND.

07:24.139 --> 07:26.184
I-IT'S IN OHIO.

07:26.271 --> 07:28.012
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

07:28.099 --> 07:29.361
OH!

07:29.449 --> 07:30.406
OH!

07:30.493 --> 07:32.147
[ BELL TINKLES ]

07:32.234 --> 07:34.758
I MADE MY FIRST BATCH
OF CHOCOLATE-CHIP COOKIES

07:34.845 --> 07:36.630
WHEN I WAS 5 YEARS OLD.

07:36.717 --> 07:38.240
I'VE NEVER LOOKED BACK.

07:38.327 --> 07:40.982
YOU SEEM PASSIONATE
ABOUT PASTRY.

07:41.069 --> 07:42.462
MM.

07:42.549 --> 07:43.985
I'M PASSIONATE
IN EVERYTHING I DO.

07:44.072 --> 07:46.683
[ BELL TINKLES ]

07:46.770 --> 07:47.858
NOTHING COMPARES TO IT.

07:47.945 --> 07:48.946
HUNTING DEER?

07:49.033 --> 07:50.513
FAWNS, ACTUALLY --
THE BABIES.

07:50.600 --> 07:52.472
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

07:52.559 --> 07:54.038
YEAH, THERE'S A CERTAIN THRILL
IN THE KILL.

07:54.125 --> 07:55.649
AND --
OH. OH, ONE SECOND.[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

07:55.736 --> 07:57.651
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

07:57.738 --> 07:58.826
OH, HO.
HEY, BUDDY!

07:58.913 --> 08:00.175
WHAT'S UP?

08:00.262 --> 08:00.958
HOLD ON.
I'M ON A DATE.HAVE A NICE DAY.

08:01.045 --> 08:02.046
SAY HI.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.526
AND SWITCH.[ BELL TINKLES ]

08:03.613 --> 08:04.658
HOW ARE YOU?

08:04.745 --> 08:07.835
OH, I WANT TO HEAR MORE
ABOUT YOU.

08:07.922 --> 08:09.924
OKAY, UM, WELL --

08:10.011 --> 08:12.274
OH, IT'S GONNA BE COLD.
IT'S COLD, ISN'T IT?

08:12.361 --> 08:13.710
OH.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.625
SO, I SPOKE WITH SELENA.
DIDN'T GET MUCH.

08:15.712 --> 08:17.322
SHE LIKES
TALL, DARK, AND HANDSOME.

08:17.409 --> 08:18.672
WELL, HOW DARK
ARE WE TALKING?

08:18.759 --> 08:20.151
[ BELL TINKLES ]

08:20.238 --> 08:21.544
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
EXCUSE ME.

08:21.631 --> 08:22.850
ONE MORE MINUTE.
ONE MORE MINUTE.

08:22.937 --> 08:24.939
I'M LOOKING FOR THAT --
THE RIGHT PERSON.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.723
AND WHAT DOES
SHE LOOK LIKE?

08:28.812 --> 08:30.031
[ BELL TINKLES ]

08:30.118 --> 08:30.945
HI. HOW ARE YOU?AH, TSH, TSH, TSH!

08:31.032 --> 08:32.163
JUST ONE MORE MINUTE.

08:32.250 --> 08:33.164
I'M JUST CHECKING
THE MAVERICKS SCORE.

08:33.251 --> 08:35.297
THEY'RE LOSING AGAIN.

08:35.384 --> 08:36.559
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S NOT GOOD.

08:36.646 --> 08:39.170
SHE'S LOOKING FOR SOMEONE
SHE CAN MANIPULATE,

08:39.257 --> 08:40.868
SOMEONE WHO COMES ACROSS
AS SINCERE

08:40.955 --> 08:41.869
BUT LESS
THAN SELF-ASSURED.

08:41.956 --> 08:42.913
HOW AM I DOING?

08:43.000 --> 08:44.262
YOU'RE GREAT.
YEAH.

08:44.349 --> 08:45.873
BASICALLY, SHE WANTS SOMEONE
WITH AN HONEST SMILE.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.701
A SMILE.

08:47.788 --> 08:48.963
THE "HONEST" PART
WENT RIGHT BY YOU, HUH?

08:50.138 --> 08:52.009
[ BELL TINKLES ]

08:52.096 --> 08:54.490
PLEASED TO MEET YOU,
MISS...

08:54.577 --> 08:55.926
OH, CALL ME SELENA.

08:56.013 --> 08:57.319
MM. SELENA.

08:57.406 --> 08:58.363
MM-HMM.

08:58.450 --> 08:59.930
I'VE GOT TO ADMIT,

09:00.017 --> 09:03.238
YOU CAUGHT MY EYE THE MINUTE
I CAME DOWN THE STAIRS.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.936
OH. [ CHUCKLES ]

09:06.023 --> 09:07.155
THAT IS A LOVELY DRESS.

09:07.242 --> 09:08.504
OH, THANK YOU.

09:08.591 --> 09:10.114
GIRL HAS TO MAKE
AN IMPRESSION, RIGHT?

09:10.201 --> 09:11.333
OH, YOU DO.
OH.

09:11.420 --> 09:13.422
TELL ME A LITTLE
ABOUT YOURSELF.

09:13.509 --> 09:15.598
WELL, FORTUNATELY,
I'VE DONE WELL --

09:15.685 --> 09:18.601
WELL ENOUGH TO DEVOTE
THE MAJORITY OF MY TIME

09:18.688 --> 09:19.950
TO A FEW NONPROFITS.

09:20.037 --> 09:21.386
MM.

09:21.473 --> 09:23.563
ARE YOU...
INTO NONPROFITING?

09:23.650 --> 09:25.042
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:25.129 --> 09:26.478
WELL, WITH THE RIGHT PERSON,
ALWAYS.

09:26.566 --> 09:28.176
YEAH?
THAT'S NICE.
MM-HMM.

09:28.263 --> 09:29.612
AND SWITCH.[ BELL TINKLES ]

09:29.699 --> 09:31.309
WELL, UH, I HOPE
WE GET TO CONTINUE

09:31.396 --> 09:32.702
THIS CONVERSATION
ANOTHER TIME.

09:32.789 --> 09:34.051
YEAH, ME TOO.
ALL RIGHT.

09:34.138 --> 09:35.313
IT WAS A LITTLE TOO FAST.

09:35.400 --> 09:36.227
IT WAS LOVELY TO MEET YOU.

09:36.314 --> 09:37.272
GREAT TO MEET YOU.

09:37.359 --> 09:38.969
Peter: HI.

09:39.056 --> 09:40.884
HI.
I'M PETER.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.451
HI, PETER.

09:42.538 --> 09:44.235
YOU'RE VERY BEAUTIFUL.

09:44.322 --> 09:46.020
AW, THANK YOU.

09:48.413 --> 09:50.677
SO, WHY ARE YOU HERE,
PETER?

09:50.764 --> 09:54.942
TO FIND SOMEONE SPECIAL.

09:55.029 --> 09:57.205
MM-HMM.

09:58.728 --> 10:01.557
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

10:01.644 --> 10:03.820
[ SIGHS ]

10:03.907 --> 10:05.517
BUT MOST OF THESE WOMEN

10:05.605 --> 10:08.216
ARE ONLY INTERESTED
IN SMALL TALK, SO...

10:08.303 --> 10:11.393
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
INTERESTED IN?

10:14.048 --> 10:15.527
BEING CAUGHT OFF GUARD.

10:15.615 --> 10:17.704
HAVING A CONVERSATION
THAT --

10:17.791 --> 10:20.184
THAT GOES BEYOND
THE "WHAT DO YOU DO?"

10:20.271 --> 10:21.882
AND "WHERE ARE YOU FROM?"

10:21.969 --> 10:27.757
SELENA, THERE ARE A LOT
OF NICE GUYS HERE.

10:27.844 --> 10:31.239
I TRULY HOPE YOU FIND THE ONE
YOU'RE WAITING FOR.

10:33.589 --> 10:35.896
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART ]

10:35.983 --> 10:38.072
SOLD FOR $8,000!
CONGRATULATIONS.

10:38.159 --> 10:39.247
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

10:41.292 --> 10:44.426
NEXT UP IS MR. ARTHUR FORT,

10:44.513 --> 10:46.950
THE PASTRY BARON OF BROOKLYN.

10:47.037 --> 10:51.955
SHALL WE START THE BIDDING
AT $5,000?

10:52.042 --> 10:53.174
$5,000.

10:53.261 --> 10:54.958
$6,000.$7,000!

10:55.045 --> 10:56.046
HE SEEMED NICE.

10:56.133 --> 10:57.395
HE WAS CHARMING.

10:57.482 --> 10:58.658
BUT?

10:58.745 --> 11:00.355
A LITTLE TOOCHARMING.

11:00.442 --> 11:02.139
$11,000.

11:02.226 --> 11:03.314
Woman: WOW.

11:03.401 --> 11:05.839
SOLD FOR $11,000.

11:05.926 --> 11:07.492
[ APPLAUSE ]

11:07.579 --> 11:11.801
OUR NEXT BACHELOR
IS MR. NICHOLAS MUNROE.

11:11.888 --> 11:14.151
NICK HAS BEEN MAKING THE ROUNDS,

11:14.238 --> 11:15.936
BUT NOW HE'S READY
TO TAKE YOU LADIES

11:16.023 --> 11:18.982
ON THE DATE OF YOUR LIVES.

11:19.069 --> 11:21.245
SHALL WE START THE BIDDING
AT $5,000?

11:21.332 --> 11:23.813
DO I HEAR $5,000?

11:23.900 --> 11:25.032
HE'S GORGEOUS.

11:25.119 --> 11:26.033
HE'S YOUNG.

11:26.120 --> 11:29.906
DO I HEAR $3,000?

11:31.821 --> 11:33.954
WELL, YOU CAN GET HIM
AT A DISCOUNT.

11:34.041 --> 11:35.346
DON'T LET ME
STAND IN YOUR WAY.

11:35.433 --> 11:37.131
HMM.

11:37.218 --> 11:39.307
1,000 BUCKS?

11:39.394 --> 11:41.483
WELL...

11:42.832 --> 11:44.878
OKAY, SOLD!

11:44.965 --> 11:47.184
[ APPLAUSE ]

11:54.583 --> 11:55.671
WHAT HAPPENED?

11:55.758 --> 11:57.064
MY PLAN WORKED.
MM.

11:57.151 --> 11:58.587
TOOWELL.

11:58.674 --> 12:00.981
OUR NEXT BACHELOR
IS MR. PETER WILLIAMS.

12:01.068 --> 12:02.722
WE'LL START THE BIDDING AT --

12:02.809 --> 12:04.724
$15,000.[ WOMEN GASP ]

12:04.811 --> 12:07.770
WOW!
ANY OTHER BIDS?

12:07.857 --> 12:11.643
SOLD FOR $15,000
TO THE WOMAN IN RED!

12:21.653 --> 12:23.612
OKAY, $15,000 HASTO BE THE RECORD.

12:23.699 --> 12:25.135
NO.
HERE YOU GO, TEX.

12:25.222 --> 12:27.311
BUT IT WAS THE SECOND-HIGHEST
BID THEY'VE EVER HAD.

12:27.398 --> 12:28.486
SECOND?

12:28.573 --> 12:30.227
THERE WAS A KENNEDY
LAST YEAR.

12:30.314 --> 12:32.273
WAS IT ONE OF
THE GOOD-LOOKING ONES?
EH...

12:32.360 --> 12:34.144
GUYS, LET'S TALK
ABOUT WHAT'S NEXT.

12:34.231 --> 12:35.537
OKAY.
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING HER?

12:35.624 --> 12:36.930
NOWHERE.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.714
I'M GONNA GO TO HER PLACE,
DROP A BUG,

12:38.801 --> 12:40.150
PLANT A KEYLOGGER,

12:40.237 --> 12:41.586
AND FIGURE OUT
WHAT SHE HAS PLANNED.

12:41.673 --> 12:42.979
AND HOW SHE PLANS
TO MURDER YOU.

12:43.066 --> 12:45.199
THAT, AND HOW SHE'S ANGLING
FOR MY MONEY.

12:45.286 --> 12:46.722
IS THIS DATE
GONNA BE DANGEROUS?

12:46.809 --> 12:48.289
WHOA.
PETER IS NOT DATING HER.

12:48.376 --> 12:49.594
I'M OCCUPYING HER.

12:49.681 --> 12:52.380
I'LL HAVE AN ARREST WARRANT
BEFORE DESSERT.

12:53.816 --> 12:55.557
HMM.

12:57.733 --> 12:58.734
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:02.346 --> 13:03.478
THIS IS PETER.

13:03.565 --> 13:04.392
SELENA:
Hey, Peter.

13:04.479 --> 13:06.394
It's Selena.

13:06.481 --> 13:07.482
HEY!
GREAT TO HEAR FROM YOU.

13:07.569 --> 13:08.570
We still on for tonight?

13:08.657 --> 13:11.747
WE HAVE RESERVATIONS
FOR 8:00 P.M.

13:11.834 --> 13:13.096
AT THE GRIFFIN.

13:13.183 --> 13:14.576
IT'S DOWNTOWN.

13:14.663 --> 13:16.056
IT'S DELICIOUS.
IT'S...

13:16.143 --> 13:18.580
I'LL PICK YOU UP AT 7:00?

13:18.667 --> 13:19.711
No.
I'll meet you there.

13:19.799 --> 13:22.018
NO, NO, NO.
I-I-IT'S NO TROUBLE.

13:22.105 --> 13:25.892
No. The trouble is you
disagreeing with me.

13:25.979 --> 13:28.068
WELL, WHAT KIND OF GENTLEMAN
WOULD I BE

13:28.155 --> 13:30.374
IF I DIDN'T PICK YOU UP
ON OUR FIRST DATE?

13:30.461 --> 13:33.116
Peter,
I'll see you at 8:00.

13:33.203 --> 13:35.075
SEE YOU AT 8:00.

13:35.162 --> 13:36.467
[ Dial tone ]

13:36.554 --> 13:37.381
NO TRACE.

13:37.468 --> 13:39.166
UGH! GREAT!

13:39.253 --> 13:40.950
WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE IS!

13:41.037 --> 13:42.386
IF I CAN'T PICK HER UP...

13:42.473 --> 13:43.779
YOU'LL HAVE TO
DROP HER OFF.

13:43.866 --> 13:44.954
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO
SEAL THE DEAL.

13:45.041 --> 13:48.131
NO -- NO, NO!
NO DEAL SEALING.

13:48.218 --> 13:49.263
YOU DON'T WANT HER
DUMPING YOU

13:49.350 --> 13:50.307
AND GOING AFTER
ANOTHER VICTIM.

13:50.394 --> 13:51.569
DIANA'S RIGHT.

13:51.656 --> 13:52.570
YOU NEED TO
IMPRESS HER ENOUGH

13:52.657 --> 13:53.876
THAT SHE WANTS TO
TAKE YOU HOME.

13:53.963 --> 13:55.922
ELIZABETH GOT ME
INTO THIS.

13:56.009 --> 13:56.923
YES, SHE DID.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.315
SO, TECHNICALLY,
IT'S OKAY.

13:58.402 --> 13:59.403
YEAH.

13:59.490 --> 14:01.101
OKAY.

14:01.188 --> 14:02.624
I'M GONNA CLOSE
THE DEAL.

14:10.893 --> 14:12.199
I'M ON POINT.

14:12.286 --> 14:14.114
TARGET'S NOT HERE.

14:14.201 --> 14:16.246
RELAX, COMMANDO.
IT IS JUST A DINNER.

14:16.333 --> 14:17.465
I GOT EYES ON SELENA.

14:17.552 --> 14:19.249
SHE'LL BE INSIDE
WITHIN A MINUTE.

14:19.336 --> 14:21.469
TARGET SIGHTED.

14:23.775 --> 14:25.255
YOU LOOK EVEN MORE
HANDSOME TONIGHT,

14:25.342 --> 14:26.300
IF THAT'S POSSIBLE.

14:26.387 --> 14:28.606
SO DO YOU.

14:28.693 --> 14:30.478
BEAUTIFUL.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:30.565 --> 14:31.827
Shall we?

14:31.914 --> 14:33.873
YES.

14:33.960 --> 14:35.483
WONDER WHAT'S
ON THE MENU.

14:35.570 --> 14:36.571
THEIRS?

14:36.658 --> 14:38.312
OR OURS?

14:39.704 --> 14:41.532
OURS.

14:41.619 --> 14:43.186
IT'S A VERY NICE HALIBUT
WITH A MANGO CHUTNEY.

14:45.275 --> 14:47.147
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

14:47.234 --> 14:49.932
YOU HELPED ME SAVE FACE
AT THE AUCTION.

14:50.019 --> 14:52.804
THE LEAST I CAN DO IS OFFER YOU
A DECENT MEAL.

14:52.892 --> 14:54.371
A CANDLE!

14:54.458 --> 14:55.372
ELECTRIC.

14:55.459 --> 14:56.765
[ LAUGHS ]

14:56.852 --> 14:57.940
SOMETHING TO DRINK?

14:58.027 --> 14:59.115
PLEASE.

14:59.202 --> 15:00.377
MAY I RECOMMEND
OUR MERLOT?

15:00.464 --> 15:02.684
A BOTTLE OF YOUR
VINO DEL DIABLO.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.468
HOW ADVENTUROUS.

15:04.555 --> 15:07.341
I'LL TAKE A RISK
ONCE IN A WHILE.

15:07.428 --> 15:08.690
LIKE THE AUCTION.

15:08.777 --> 15:09.778
LIKE YOU.

15:09.865 --> 15:11.519
OH, SO I'M A RISK?

15:11.606 --> 15:13.390
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:13.477 --> 15:16.480
I FEEL I DON'T NEED TO HIDE
ANYTHING FROM YOU.

15:16.567 --> 15:19.396
OH.

15:19.483 --> 15:21.529
MAYBE THAT WAS
A LITTLE TOO FORWARD.

15:21.616 --> 15:23.096
NO, PETER.

15:23.183 --> 15:25.272
THERE'S NOTHING MORE ATTRACTIVE
THAN THE TRUTH.

15:25.359 --> 15:26.316
MM.

15:26.403 --> 15:28.666
HE'S DOING GOOD.

15:28.753 --> 15:30.059
WELL, HE'S GONNA NEED
TO STEP IT UP

15:30.146 --> 15:31.452
IF HE WANTS AN INVITE BACK
TO HER PLACE.

15:31.539 --> 15:32.757
YOU EVER COOK LIKE THIS
FOR SARA?

15:32.844 --> 15:34.455
I THOUGHT ABOUT IT.

15:34.542 --> 15:36.718
WELL, DO MORE THAN THINK.

15:36.805 --> 15:39.590
INSURANCE INVESTIGATOR BARBIE
WOULD BE THOROUGHLY IMPRESSED.

15:39.677 --> 15:41.375
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

15:41.462 --> 15:42.811
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

15:42.898 --> 15:44.204
[ CHUCKLES ][ SLOW MUSIC PLAYS ]

15:44.291 --> 15:46.119
OH, I LOVE THIS SONG.

15:46.206 --> 15:47.816
OH, ME TOO.

15:47.903 --> 15:49.383
SHALL WE DANCE?

15:49.470 --> 15:51.080
OH, UH...

15:51.167 --> 15:52.560
YOU'VE BEEN ADVENTUROUS
WITH THE MERLOT.

15:52.647 --> 15:53.648
WHY STOP NOW?

15:53.735 --> 15:54.649
[ STAMMERS, CHUCKLES ]

15:54.736 --> 15:56.564
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

16:03.658 --> 16:06.922
[ TANGO PLAYS ]

16:07.009 --> 16:08.228
IS THAT A TANGO?

16:08.315 --> 16:09.359
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

16:09.446 --> 16:11.013
PETER, PETER,
THERE ARE CERTAIN THINGS

16:11.100 --> 16:12.406
you cannot recover from.

16:14.408 --> 16:16.236
I CAN HANDLE THIS.

16:27.899 --> 16:29.423
I DON'T HEAR
ANY SCREAMING.

16:31.294 --> 16:33.601
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

16:43.350 --> 16:45.004
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

16:55.797 --> 16:56.841
[ MUSIC ENDS ]

16:56.928 --> 16:58.626
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

16:59.975 --> 17:02.586
LET'S GO BACK
TO MY APARTMENT SO THAT --

17:02.673 --> 17:04.327
[ FEEDBACK ]WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

17:04.414 --> 17:05.633
DID YOU GET THAT?

17:05.720 --> 17:07.069
THE FIRST PART
LOUD AND CLEAR.

17:07.156 --> 17:08.984
THE SECOND?NEVER TO BE REPEATED.

17:09.071 --> 17:10.377
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:10.464 --> 17:12.727
NICE WORK, AGENT BURKE.

17:12.814 --> 17:14.250
PETER.

17:14.337 --> 17:16.731
REMIND ME TO THANK EL
FOR THE DANCE LESSONS.

17:16.818 --> 17:18.341
NEAL? NEAL?

17:18.428 --> 17:20.039
Neal?

17:20.126 --> 17:21.127
I DON'T THINK
HE CAN HEAR US.

17:21.214 --> 17:22.389
SHE MUST HAVE BLOWN
THE RECEIVER.

17:26.915 --> 17:29.178
Selena:
WHY DON'T YOU MAKE US A DRINK

17:29.265 --> 17:31.180
WHILE I CHANGE
AND PUT ON SOME MUSIC?

17:33.356 --> 17:35.315
IS SHE ACTUALLY SLIPPING
INTO SOMETHING MORE COMFORTABLE?

17:35.402 --> 17:36.272
MM-HMM.

17:36.359 --> 17:37.404
I DON'T LIKE THIS WOMAN.

17:37.491 --> 17:38.753
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]

17:38.840 --> 17:40.233
HEY, JONES.
WHAT'S UP?

17:40.320 --> 17:43.236
COME ON, PETER.
PLANT THE BUG AND GET OUT.

17:43.323 --> 17:44.759
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

17:44.846 --> 17:47.153
IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,
I DON'T SEE A COMPUTER,

17:47.240 --> 17:50.199
SO THE KEYLOGGER
ISN'T GONNA WORK.

17:55.726 --> 17:57.685
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.078 --> 18:02.603
I'M GOING FOR THE BUG PLANT
ON THE PURSE.

18:02.690 --> 18:03.560
THANKS, JONES.

18:03.647 --> 18:05.171
L.A.'s AUTOPSY CAME IN.

18:05.258 --> 18:07.695
SELENA'S FOURTH VICTIM DEAD
OF A STAB WOUND TO THE THROAT.

18:07.782 --> 18:09.523
STREET MUGGING.

18:09.610 --> 18:10.611
SELENA WAS
THE ONLY EYEWITNESS,

18:10.698 --> 18:11.655
AND THEY NEVER CAUGHT
THE ASSAILANT.

18:11.742 --> 18:12.656
WELL, THAT'S CONVENIENT.

18:12.743 --> 18:13.701
THE MURDER HAPPENED

18:13.788 --> 18:14.658
WHILE THEY WERE OUT
TO DINNER.

18:14.745 --> 18:16.095
MAYBE SHE IS
A SERIAL KILLER.

18:16.182 --> 18:17.400
OR HE CAUGHT ON
TO HER PLAN.

18:21.578 --> 18:22.536
MM.

18:22.623 --> 18:24.320
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

18:24.407 --> 18:26.235
THOUGHT I SAW A BUG.

18:26.322 --> 18:28.498
I'LL CALL THE EXTERMINATOR
IN THE MORNING.

18:28.585 --> 18:30.196
HOW ABOUT THOSE DRINKS?

18:40.162 --> 18:41.424
LEMON?

18:41.511 --> 18:43.557
SURPRISE ME.

18:59.138 --> 19:00.269
PETER?

19:00.356 --> 19:01.357
YES.

19:02.837 --> 19:04.795
[ BOTH CHUCKLING ]

19:09.409 --> 19:11.280
OH! OH!

19:11.367 --> 19:14.153
OH, OH,
I JUST SPILLED IT ON ME.
OH!

19:14.240 --> 19:15.154
Oh, I'm so clumsy.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.372
HE NEEDS HELP.

19:16.459 --> 19:17.939
ALL RIGHT,
I'M GONNA CALL HIM.

19:18.026 --> 19:19.636
CAN YOU GENERATE
SOME SOUND EFFECTS?

19:19.723 --> 19:21.856
A STEEL MILL,
PEOPLE YELLING, SOMETHING.

19:21.943 --> 19:23.684
THE BUREAU CAN, AND I CAN PATCH
IT THROUGH TO THE CALL.

19:23.771 --> 19:25.207
YOU MIND
IF I USE YOUR BATHROOM?

19:25.294 --> 19:26.904
OH, NO,
I CAN HELP YOU WITH THAT.

19:26.991 --> 19:28.689
OH, NO, NO. THAT'S OKAY.
I --

19:28.776 --> 19:30.212
THESE BUTTONS ARE DIFFICULT.
LET ME --

19:30.299 --> 19:32.823
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

19:32.910 --> 19:34.956
UH, HERE,
LET ME GET THE --

19:35.043 --> 19:36.349
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]OH, OH...

19:36.436 --> 19:37.872
NO, NO -- I CAN GET IT.
THAT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

19:37.959 --> 19:39.700
[ GASPS ]

19:39.787 --> 19:41.223
PETER WILLIAMS' PHONE.

19:41.310 --> 19:43.007
NEAL:
Where's Mr. Williams?

19:43.094 --> 19:45.184
WHO IS THIS?
YOU KNOW WHAT?[ Machinery grinding ]

19:45.271 --> 19:46.620
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

19:46.707 --> 19:49.057
We need him here, pronto.

19:49.144 --> 19:50.972
Hamilton mill is getting lit up
like a Christmas tree.

19:51.059 --> 19:53.017
We have an induction furnace
that is ready to blow.

19:53.104 --> 19:56.369
SOUNDS IMPORTANT.

19:56.456 --> 19:58.849
THIS IS WILLIAMS.

19:58.936 --> 20:00.634
HELLO, MR. WILLIAMS.

20:00.721 --> 20:03.463
I'M LOOKING FOR PHIL --
PHIL LANDERER.

20:03.550 --> 20:04.681
RIGHT.

20:04.768 --> 20:05.726
You know him?

20:05.813 --> 20:06.814
OKAY, ON MY WAY.

20:06.901 --> 20:09.208
WE'RE GOOD.

20:10.731 --> 20:13.037
SORRY.
I GOT TO HANDLE THIS.

20:13.124 --> 20:14.735
OH...
I KNOW IT.

20:14.822 --> 20:16.911
I KNOW.
SELENA, I HAD A GREAT TIME.

20:16.998 --> 20:18.434
I'LL MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

20:18.521 --> 20:20.480
OH, YOU'LL MAKE IT UP TO ME
TOMORROW NIGHT.

20:20.567 --> 20:22.177
MMM.

20:24.832 --> 20:27.400
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

20:27.487 --> 20:28.314
GOTTA GO.
YEAH.

20:31.447 --> 20:33.014
HMM.

20:37.845 --> 20:40.326
SELENA MADE A CALL
AFTER YOU LEFT.

20:40.413 --> 20:42.850
I'M PULLING UP THE AUDIO NOW.
HANG ON.

20:42.937 --> 20:45.156
Selena: IT'S ME.

20:45.244 --> 20:46.810
HE LEFT EARLY,
BUT I THINK I GOT TO HIM.

20:46.897 --> 20:47.768
Man:
DID YOU SPOOK HIM?

20:47.855 --> 20:49.596
NOT AT ALL.

20:49.683 --> 20:50.988
I'LL HAVE WILLIAMS
DOWN ON ONE KNEE

20:51.075 --> 20:52.512
BY THE END OF THE WEEK.

20:52.599 --> 20:55.210
AFTER THAT, YOU FINISH THE JOB, AND IT'S PAYDAY.

20:55.297 --> 20:57.343
SHE HAS A PARTNER.

20:57.430 --> 21:00.041
WHOEVER HER PARTNER IS,
THEY PROBABLY RUN THE ENDGAME.

21:00.128 --> 21:01.608
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO KEEP SEEING HER.

21:01.695 --> 21:02.696
IS THERE ANOTHER OPTION?

21:02.783 --> 21:04.698
ANYONE?

21:04.785 --> 21:07.962
I'M SURE ELIZABETH WILL BE
COMPLETELY...SUPPORTIVE.

21:08.049 --> 21:09.355
MM-HMM.

21:09.442 --> 21:10.617
WE'LL FIND OUT
WHEN WE TALK TO HER.

21:10.704 --> 21:12.227
"WE"?
YES, WE.

21:12.314 --> 21:14.098
OH, COME ON.

21:14.185 --> 21:15.883
WHY DO YOU HAVE TO
SEE HER AGAIN?

21:15.970 --> 21:19.756
WE'VE RUN INTO
SOME...COMPLICATIONS, BUT --

21:19.843 --> 21:22.019
ELIZABETH, THIS --
THIS WOMAN IS A MURDERER.

21:22.106 --> 21:23.847
ANOTHER REASON
I DON'T LOVE THIS!

21:23.934 --> 21:25.153
SHE NEEDS TO BE TAKEN OUT.

21:25.240 --> 21:26.241
DOWN.
DOWN.

21:26.328 --> 21:27.590
SHE NEEDS TO BE
TAKEN DOWN.

21:27.677 --> 21:30.985
EL, I WANT THIS OVER WITH
MORE THAN ANYONE.

21:31.072 --> 21:34.205
IS SHE...ATTRACTIVE?

21:34.293 --> 21:36.033
NOT REALLY.DEFINE "ATTRACTIVE."

21:36.120 --> 21:37.383
YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA --

21:37.470 --> 21:38.949
I'M GONNA TAKE SATCHMO
FOR A WALK,

21:39.036 --> 21:39.950
GET A LITTLE AIR.

21:45.521 --> 21:47.349
BYE.

21:47.436 --> 21:48.611
SEE YA, HONEY.

21:50.831 --> 21:52.659
THAT WASN'T A COMPLETE
TRAIN WRECK.

21:52.746 --> 21:54.269
BUT THAT'S AS FAR
AS IT GOES.

21:54.356 --> 21:56.271
YOU'RE SEEING SELENA
AGAIN TONIGHT.

21:56.358 --> 21:57.620
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

21:57.707 --> 21:59.927
WELL, I'M GONNA TRY
TO GET TO HER CELL PHONE

22:00.014 --> 22:02.059
AND FIND OUT
WHO SHE'S TALKING WITH.

22:02.146 --> 22:03.583
THE SOONER THIS ENDS,
THE BETTER.

22:03.670 --> 22:05.454
THEN PROPOSE.
RIGHT. WHAT?

22:05.541 --> 22:07.326
WELL, YOU SAID YOU WANT
TO SPEED THINGS UP, RIGHT?

22:07.413 --> 22:08.805
YEAH.
NOTHING SAYS
"ENAMORED" LIKE --

22:08.892 --> 22:09.632
POLYGAMY?

22:09.719 --> 22:10.720
"MARRY ME."
NO!

22:10.807 --> 22:13.114
NO, THE CELL
IS A GOOD START.

22:13.201 --> 22:14.768
ALL RIGHT,
IT'S YOUR OPERATION.

22:14.855 --> 22:16.160
AND I'M NOT CHANGING IT.

22:16.247 --> 22:18.075
DIANA HAS ALREADY
PREPPED THE TEAM.

22:18.162 --> 22:19.816
SHE'S FOLLOWING ME
IN THE VAN.

22:19.903 --> 22:20.904
SOUNDS LIKE
YOU GOT IT COVERED.

22:20.991 --> 22:21.775
DO YOU MIND
IF I TAKE OFF?

22:21.862 --> 22:22.906
WHERE YOU GOING?

22:22.993 --> 22:24.255
SARA'S COMING
TO MY PLACE.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.648
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
WITH DINNER PLANS.

22:28.825 --> 22:30.349
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

22:30.436 --> 22:31.567
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

22:35.658 --> 22:37.704
HEY.

22:37.791 --> 22:39.270
HEY, I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

22:39.358 --> 22:40.968
I DON'T KNOW.

22:41.055 --> 22:42.448
YOU TELL ME.

22:45.712 --> 22:46.843
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:49.585 --> 22:52.066
YOU'RE TRYING
TO IMPRESS ME.

22:52.153 --> 22:55.330
WELL, LOOK, I KNOW YOU SAID
I DIDN'T HAVE TO, BUT...

22:55.417 --> 22:57.376
WHATEVER MAKES YOU
FEEL BETTER.

23:01.989 --> 23:04.557
WOW. LOOK AT YOU.

23:04.644 --> 23:06.341
NO PURSE?
NO.

23:06.428 --> 23:07.734
I WAS IN THE MOOD
FOR SOMETHING

23:07.821 --> 23:09.213
A LITTLE MORE
PRIVATE TONIGHT.

23:09.300 --> 23:10.389
LET'S GO TO YOUR PLACE.

23:10.476 --> 23:11.955
MY PLACE?

23:12.042 --> 23:13.914
MM-HMM.

23:14.001 --> 23:16.003
SURE. SOUNDS GOOD.

23:16.090 --> 23:17.700
OH, IT WILL BE.

23:24.794 --> 23:26.405
[ Dialing ]

23:26.492 --> 23:28.058
NEAL, CHANGE OF PLANS.

23:28.145 --> 23:31.105
YOU HAVE 15 MINUTES TO CLEAR OUT
OF YOUR APARTMENT,

23:31.192 --> 23:32.541
OR MY COVER'S BLOWN.

23:32.628 --> 23:34.587
I'M COMMANDEERING
YOUR DATE.

23:34.674 --> 23:37.328
[ CELL PHONE BUZZING ]

23:43.596 --> 23:46.425
IT'S VERY LOVELY
FOR A FIRST DATE.

23:46.512 --> 23:48.165
DON'T EXPECT THIS
EVERY TIME.

23:48.252 --> 23:49.689
OH, THERE'S GONNA BE
A SECOND DATE?

23:49.776 --> 23:50.820
GUY CAN HOPE.

23:50.907 --> 23:51.995
YEAH?
YEAH.

23:52.082 --> 23:53.344
I COULD BE TALKED
INTO IT.

23:53.432 --> 23:55.303
[ CELL PHONE BUZZING ]NEAL,
GO CHECK YOUR PHONE.

23:55.390 --> 23:56.391
THANK YOU.
YEP.

24:03.703 --> 24:05.313
[ SIGHS ]
WHO IS IT?

24:05.400 --> 24:07.315
WE GOT TO GET OUT
OF HERE RIGHT NOW.

24:07.402 --> 24:09.622
PETER'S UNDERCOVER.
HE'S COMING UP THE STAIRS.

24:09.709 --> 24:10.884
I'LL EXPLAIN EVERYTHING
LATER.

24:10.971 --> 24:12.538
NO, NO! NOT THAT WAY!
THE CLOSET.

24:12.625 --> 24:13.452
UH, NEW BOTTLE.

24:14.801 --> 24:16.106
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:16.193 --> 24:17.934
THROUGH THERE.

24:18.021 --> 24:20.241
[ PETER TALKING INDISTINCTLY ]I GOT IT, I GOT IT.

24:20.328 --> 24:22.548
SORRY.

24:22.635 --> 24:24.854
Sara:
OOH, GRAB ME A QUICHE.

24:24.941 --> 24:28.379
JUST LET ME MAKE SURE
WE'RE ALL SET.

24:32.688 --> 24:35.038
HERE WE ARE.

24:35.125 --> 24:36.518
[ GASPS ]

24:36.605 --> 24:38.564
AMAZING!

24:38.651 --> 24:40.348
HUH.

24:40.435 --> 24:42.045
OH, PETER,
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE.

24:42.132 --> 24:44.526
[ CHUCKLES ]
SURPRISE.

24:44.613 --> 24:45.658
WHAT IS GOING ON?

24:45.745 --> 24:47.573
REMEMBER THAT CASE
I WAS WORKING ON?

24:47.660 --> 24:48.835
THE KILLER BRIDE?

24:48.922 --> 24:50.576
YEAH.
PETER'S DATING HER NOW.

24:50.663 --> 24:51.707
REALLY?
YEP.

24:51.794 --> 24:53.317
SO WHAT ARE WEDOING?

24:53.404 --> 24:56.103
THIS APARTMENT
WAS A BACKROOM SPEAKEASY.

24:56.190 --> 25:00.673
AND THIS WAS
THE OBSERVATION ROOM.

25:00.760 --> 25:02.979
OH, WOW.
Selena:
VERY ECLECTIC, RIGHT?

25:03.066 --> 25:05.939
PETER, YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
THAT YOU WERE AN ARTIST.

25:06.026 --> 25:07.244
I DABBLE.

25:07.331 --> 25:09.072
I WOULDN'T SAY
I'M ANY GOOD, THOUGH.

25:09.159 --> 25:10.683
OH, DON'T BE MODEST.

25:10.770 --> 25:12.989
YOU KNOW,
THIS MAY SOUND SILLY, BUT...

25:14.904 --> 25:16.515
...WOULD YOU DRAW ME?

25:16.602 --> 25:18.952
OH, I'M SURE
THAT WE COULD HAVE...

25:20.475 --> 25:22.346
YOU MEAN RIGHT NOW?

25:22.433 --> 25:24.044
YEAH. WHY NOT?

25:24.131 --> 25:26.873
I-IT WOULD TAKE TIME
TO DO IT RIGHT.

25:26.960 --> 25:28.962
WE HAVE ALL NIGHT.

25:29.049 --> 25:31.617
IT WOULDN'T
DO YOU JUSTICE.

25:31.704 --> 25:34.097
OH, BUT YOU WILL.
I WON'T TAKE NO FOR AN ANSWER.

25:34.184 --> 25:37.013
OKAY.

25:37.100 --> 25:38.928
BUT, UH...

25:39.015 --> 25:41.583
YOU SHOULD KNOW
THAT I'M EXPERIMENTING

25:41.670 --> 25:44.107
WITH SOME VERY, VERY
PRIMITIVE STYLES.

25:44.194 --> 25:45.500
OOH.
[ Chuckling ] YEAH.

25:47.720 --> 25:49.243
CANPETER DRAW?

25:49.330 --> 25:51.985
UNLESS SHE'S EXPECTING
A BREATHTAKING STICK FIGURE,

25:52.072 --> 25:52.986
HE'S IN TROUBLE.

25:53.073 --> 25:54.596
UH-HUH.

25:54.683 --> 25:56.076
DOES HE KNOW
THAT YOU'REHERE?

25:56.163 --> 25:57.904
UNFORTUNATELY, YES,
HE KNOWS ABOUT THIS ROOM.

25:57.991 --> 25:59.514
ALL RIGHT.

25:59.601 --> 26:01.734
[ SELENA SIGHS ]

26:01.821 --> 26:05.259
LET ME MAKE SURE
THE LIGHT IS RIGHT.

26:09.872 --> 26:12.919
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

26:13.006 --> 26:15.008
HOLD THIS.

26:19.839 --> 26:22.624
THIS IS NOT HOW I SAW
THE NIGHT GOING, BY THE WAY.

26:22.711 --> 26:23.973
OH.

26:24.060 --> 26:26.367
I MEAN, ANY GUY
CAN MAKE A GIRL DINNER.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.064
ONLY YOUCOULD SKETCH
A BLACK WIDOW

26:28.151 --> 26:29.762
FROM A HIDDEN BACK ROOM.

26:29.849 --> 26:31.198
IS THE POSE OKAY?

26:31.285 --> 26:33.417
YES. THAT'S PERFECT.
OKAY.

26:33.504 --> 26:35.202
BUT, REMEMBER --
NO PEEKING.

26:35.289 --> 26:36.551
PETER, I HAVE TO ASK,

26:36.638 --> 26:38.509
HOW DID YOU...

26:38.597 --> 26:40.903
SET THIS...
ALL UP SO FAST?

26:40.990 --> 26:42.949
UM...

26:43.036 --> 26:46.517
HEY, DO YOURSELF A FAVOR.

26:46.605 --> 26:49.912
NEVER TRY TO SEND A GRAPPLING
HOOK THROUGH THE POST OFFICE.

26:52.306 --> 26:54.569
I-I MEAN, THAT IS, IF...

26:54.656 --> 26:57.746
YOU EVER NEEDED TO SEND...
A GRAPPLING HOOK, THAT IS.

26:57.833 --> 27:00.140
PERFECT TIMING.

27:00.227 --> 27:03.012
THIS IS MY...MAN --
HAVERSHAM.

27:03.099 --> 27:04.753
HE MADE THE ARRANGEMENTS.

27:04.840 --> 27:06.886
HAVERSHAM,
EVERYTHING IS PERFECT.

27:06.973 --> 27:07.974
THANK YOU.

27:08.061 --> 27:10.585
YOU MAY ENJOY
YOUR NIGHT OFF.

27:10.672 --> 27:12.456
SO SORRY TO INTERRUPT...

27:12.543 --> 27:15.155
SUCH A SUSPICIOUSLY
AMOROUS EVENING.

27:15.242 --> 27:17.287
HAVERSHAM, DO YOU MIND?

27:17.374 --> 27:19.812
I'LL NEED MY SUIT
FOR TOMORROW.

27:19.899 --> 27:22.553
A SUIT.

27:22.641 --> 27:24.338
YES.

27:24.425 --> 27:27.210
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

27:27.297 --> 27:28.647
GOOD.

27:28.734 --> 27:30.083
HOW HANDY.

27:30.170 --> 27:33.608
YES,
HE'S...ONE OF A KIND.

27:35.436 --> 27:37.656
I SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.

27:37.743 --> 27:39.222
FINISHED.

27:39.309 --> 27:40.789
IT LOOKS GOOD.

27:40.876 --> 27:42.965
HMM.

27:43.052 --> 27:44.140
SOMETHING'S MISSING.

27:46.055 --> 27:47.970
NEAL, ARE YOU SURE
YOU WANT TO DO THAT?

27:48.057 --> 27:50.103
WELL, PETER SAID HE WANTS
THIS CASE CLOSED FAST.

27:50.190 --> 27:51.452
THIS SHOULD HELP.

27:51.539 --> 27:53.019
OKAY, BUT PETER
IS GONNA BE REALLYMAD.

27:53.106 --> 27:54.498
BUT SHEWON'T.

27:54.585 --> 27:58.241
ALL RIGHT, MOZ, GET THIS TO HIM
WITHOUT HER SEEING.

27:58.328 --> 27:59.721
OH, SURE.

27:59.808 --> 28:01.810
I'LL HIDE IT UNDER
MY GARGANTUAN CLOWN SLEEVE.

28:01.897 --> 28:04.465
OH, COME HERE.
TRY THIS.

28:04.552 --> 28:06.380
OH, I'M MORE OF A SPRING.

28:06.467 --> 28:07.773
MOZ, WE DON'T HAVE TIME.

28:07.860 --> 28:10.776
OKAY. OH.
I GOT IT.
OKAY.

28:12.821 --> 28:14.127
[ SIGHS ]

28:16.869 --> 28:21.351
YOUR TURNCOAT
FOR TOMORROW, SIR.

28:21.438 --> 28:22.657
AH, YES.
THANK YOU.

28:22.744 --> 28:24.267
THAT IS EXACTLY
WHAT I NEEDED.

28:24.354 --> 28:25.616
MM.

28:27.575 --> 28:28.489
GOOD WORK, MOZ.

28:28.576 --> 28:30.404
OH, I'M GONNA NEED SOME...

28:30.491 --> 28:32.623
CASH FOR THE DRY-CLEANER.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.538
OF COURSE.
$50 SHOULD DO IT.

28:34.625 --> 28:37.541
DON'T KNOW WHAT I'D DO
WITHOUT YOU.

28:37.628 --> 28:39.630
OH, I MIGHT NEED MORE.

28:41.502 --> 28:42.721
AH. GOOD EVENING...

28:42.808 --> 28:44.200
YES.
...MADAM.

28:44.287 --> 28:46.637
IT'S GREAT TO MEET YOU...
HAVERSHAM.

28:46.725 --> 28:47.551
[ GIGGLES ]

28:51.468 --> 28:53.601
HE'S CURIOUS.

28:53.688 --> 28:56.604
VERY HIGH-FUNCTIONING,
CONSIDERING HIS CONDITION.

28:56.691 --> 28:59.215
OH.

28:59.302 --> 29:02.088
DONE.

29:02.175 --> 29:03.872
[ PETER CHUCKLES ]

29:03.959 --> 29:08.224
[ GASPS ] WOW!
THAT LOOKS AMAZING!

29:08.311 --> 29:11.271
YEAH, IT IS.

29:11.358 --> 29:12.751
PETER, WHAT'S THIS?

29:12.838 --> 29:13.882
OH, THAT?

29:16.058 --> 29:17.059
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]

29:17.146 --> 29:20.410
I WANTED TONIGHT
TO BE SPECIAL.

29:20.497 --> 29:24.937
ARE YOU ASKING ME WHAT I THINK
YOU'RE ASKING ME?

29:25.024 --> 29:26.373
OH...
OH!

29:26.460 --> 29:28.027
PETER! YES.

29:28.114 --> 29:29.855
YES, YES.

29:32.248 --> 29:35.077
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

29:35.164 --> 29:37.340
BEST DATE EVER.

29:40.779 --> 29:42.302
SHE SAID YES?!

29:42.389 --> 29:45.044
YOU COULD LOOK AT THIS AS
ANOTHER VICTORY FOR TEAM BURKE.

29:45.131 --> 29:46.045
BUH.

29:46.132 --> 29:47.394
EH, EL,

29:47.481 --> 29:49.222
I'M PUTTING MY LIFE
AT RISK HERE.

29:49.309 --> 29:50.701
YES! YOU ARE.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.878
I MEAN, THIS WAS --
THIS WAS SUPPOSED TO BE A DATE,

29:52.965 --> 29:54.053
NOT A "SAVE THE DATE."

29:54.140 --> 29:55.750
THE INVESTIGATION'S
ALMOST OVER.

29:55.837 --> 29:57.534
YEAH, I RECALL HEARING THAT
AFTER THE FIRST DATE.

29:57.621 --> 29:58.971
NOW YOU'RE ENGAGED?

29:59.058 --> 30:02.278
ALL I NEED IS TO FIND OUT
WHO HER PARTNER IS.

30:02.365 --> 30:05.412
THAT MEANS CONTACTS,
FIGURING OUT WHO SHE'S CLOSE TO.

30:05.499 --> 30:07.196
MAYBE YOU NEED
A GUEST LIST.

30:07.283 --> 30:08.328
GUEST LIST?

30:08.415 --> 30:09.895
FOR THE WEDDING.

30:09.982 --> 30:12.680
YOU WANT TO WRAP UP
THIS CASE?

30:12.767 --> 30:13.899
YOU NEED
AN EVENT PLANNER.

30:18.207 --> 30:19.687
LOOK AT YOU TWO.

30:19.774 --> 30:21.907
PETER, YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
SHE WAS SO BEAUTIFUL.

30:21.994 --> 30:23.473
[ CHUCKLES ]
THANK YOU.

30:23.560 --> 30:25.084
MM, YOU'RE SO WELCOME.

30:25.171 --> 30:27.695
NOW, I WAS THINKING OF SETTING
YOU GUYS UP BY THE GAZEBO.

30:27.782 --> 30:29.523
OH. THAT SOUNDS GREAT.YEAH.

30:29.610 --> 30:31.568
I'LL NEED A HEAD COUNT TO MAKE
SURE WE HAVE ENOUGH ROOM.

30:31.655 --> 30:32.656
DID YOU BRING YOUR LISTS?

30:32.743 --> 30:34.745
SELENA,
FRIENDS AND FAMILY?

30:34.833 --> 30:36.704
OH, NO.
I'M NEW TO THE CITY.

30:36.791 --> 30:38.097
I DON'T KNOW
MANY PEOPLE HERE.

30:38.184 --> 30:41.187
PLUS, I HAVE ALL THE FAMILY
I NEED IN THIS MAN.

30:41.274 --> 30:42.101
[ CHUCKLES WEAKLY ]

30:43.929 --> 30:46.627
I UNDERSTAND.
YOU WANT TO KEEP IT SMALL.

30:46.714 --> 30:48.368
WEDDINGS CAN BE
SO CHAOTIC.

30:48.455 --> 30:49.760
IN THE END,

30:49.848 --> 30:52.241
YOU'RE MAKING A SCHEDULE
INSTEAD OF A-A MEMORY.

30:52.328 --> 30:53.939
SOUNDS LIKE
YOU'VE HAD EXPERIENCE.

30:54.026 --> 30:56.593
YOU KNOW, MY HUSBAND AND I
WANTED TO KEEP IT SMALL,

30:56.680 --> 30:58.421
BUT SOMEHOW OUR WEDDING
BALLOONED

30:58.508 --> 30:59.727
INTO THIS MASSIVE EVENT.

30:59.814 --> 31:01.860
YOU DIDN'T ENJOY IT?

31:01.947 --> 31:05.341
OH, IT WAS LOVELY.
IT WAS REALLY LOVELY.

31:05.428 --> 31:07.387
BUT I THINK
IF I WERE TO DO IT AGAIN,

31:07.474 --> 31:09.519
I'D KEEP IT A LITTLE MORE
INTIMATE, SIMPLE.

31:09.606 --> 31:11.043
JUST US.

31:11.130 --> 31:15.221
WELL, HOPEFULLY,
OURS WILL BE MORE SPECIAL.

31:15.308 --> 31:17.919
MM...WE...
HAVE TO GET GOING.

31:18.006 --> 31:20.617
WE HAVE RESERVATIONS FOR LUNCH
IN A HALF-HOUR.

31:20.704 --> 31:22.532
OH, PETER, DO YOU MIND IF I
BORROW SELENA FOR JUST A MOMENT?

31:22.619 --> 31:24.752
I WOULD LOVETO GO OVER
INVITATIONS WITH HER.

31:24.839 --> 31:26.580
SURE.
I'LL GO GET THE CAR.

31:26.667 --> 31:28.712
OKAY.
THANKS, HONEY.

31:28.799 --> 31:30.801
UM...
NOW THAT WE'RE ALONE,

31:30.889 --> 31:33.239
I WANTED TO ASK
YOU SOMETHING,

31:33.326 --> 31:35.502
AND I DIDN'T WANT TO DO IT
IN FRONT OF YOUR FIANCé.

31:35.589 --> 31:38.200
UM...HAVE YOU BEEN
MARRIED BEFORE?

31:38.287 --> 31:40.724
I HAVE.

31:40.811 --> 31:42.422
HOW MANY TIMES?

31:42.509 --> 31:43.858
WHAT BUSINESS
IS THAT OF YOURS?

31:43.945 --> 31:45.468
OH, I WAS JUST ASKING
TO MAKE SURE

31:45.555 --> 31:47.340
THAT YOU HAVE ALL
THE PROPER LEGAL DOCUMENTS

31:47.427 --> 31:48.602
FOR THE MARRIAGE LICENSE.

31:48.689 --> 31:50.952
THAT WAY, WE CAN AVOID
A LOT OF QUESTIONS.

31:51.039 --> 31:52.345
GREAT.

31:52.432 --> 31:54.216
I'LL HAVE MY LAWYER
SEND OVER THE PAPERS.

31:58.873 --> 32:01.136
OKAY.
SO, WE'LL BE IN TOUCH.

32:01.223 --> 32:02.485
THANK YOU SO MUCH.OKAY.

32:02.572 --> 32:03.747
READY?

32:03.834 --> 32:05.358
READY AS YOU ARE.

32:15.498 --> 32:17.109
[ ENGINE REVS, TIRES SCREECH ]

32:17.196 --> 32:18.284
Elizabeth: PETER!

32:22.941 --> 32:24.507
DID YOU, UH -- DID YOU GET
A LOOK AT THE LICENSE PLATE?

32:24.594 --> 32:25.944
UH, NO TAGS.

32:26.031 --> 32:27.510
ALL RIGHT,
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.

32:27.597 --> 32:29.121
I GOT IT FROM HERE.

32:29.208 --> 32:30.818
THANK YOU.

32:30.905 --> 32:33.560
WOW. THAT CAR
CAME OUT OF NOWHERE.

32:35.040 --> 32:37.868
YEAH.

32:37.956 --> 32:39.740
IF SHE HADN'T WARNED ME,
I --

32:39.827 --> 32:41.916
OH, I DON'T WANT
TO THINK ABOUT THAT.

32:42.003 --> 32:44.397
I-I DON'T KNOW WHAT I WOULD DO
IF ANYTHING HAPPENED TO YOU.

32:44.484 --> 32:46.965
AND IF SOMETHING DID?

32:47.052 --> 32:48.749
[ SIGHS ]

32:50.316 --> 32:51.839
HOW CLOSE WAS IT?
CLOSE.

32:51.926 --> 32:53.232
GOT MY HEART PUMPING.

32:53.319 --> 32:55.495
BUT THEN SELENA AND I
HAD ONE OF THOSE

32:55.582 --> 32:57.714
"SHOULD ANYTHING
EVER HAPPEN" CHATS.

32:57.801 --> 32:59.368
OH. THAT'S
A PRETTY GOOD SCAM.

32:59.455 --> 33:01.022
CAR NEARLY RUNS YOU DOWN,

33:01.109 --> 33:03.764
WHICH PROMPTS A DISCUSSION ABOUT
WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU'RE GONE?

33:03.851 --> 33:05.113
EXACTLY.

33:05.200 --> 33:06.985
SHE TOLD ME
IF WORSE COMES TO WORSE,

33:07.072 --> 33:08.595
SHE WOULDN'T WANT A DIME
OF MY MONEY.

33:08.682 --> 33:09.857
REALLY?

33:09.944 --> 33:11.685
SHE'D PREFER I LEAVE IT
TO CHARITY.

33:11.772 --> 33:12.903
ONE OF HER CHOOSING?

33:12.991 --> 33:16.342
I WENT THROUGH THE WILLS
OF HER VICTIMS.

33:16.429 --> 33:18.909
EACH ONE LEFT
A SIGNIFICANT CONTRIBUTION

33:18.997 --> 33:20.868
TO A CHARITABLE
ORGANIZATION.

33:20.955 --> 33:23.001
I'M GUESSING
THESE DON'T EXIST ANYMORE.

33:23.088 --> 33:24.567
NO.
SO WHERE'D THE MONEY GO?

33:24.654 --> 33:26.265
THIS MAY TELL US.

33:26.352 --> 33:28.397
WE GOT SOMETHING
FROM THE LEGAL PAPERS

33:28.484 --> 33:30.095
SELENA GAVE ELIZABETH.

33:30.182 --> 33:32.532
THE LAWYER'S NAME WAS A BOGUS
I.D. WE TRACKED TO THIS GUY.

33:32.619 --> 33:34.273
LOOK FAMILIAR?

33:34.360 --> 33:36.144
IT'S THE EMCEE
FROM THE AUCTION.GERALD JAMESON.

33:36.231 --> 33:38.146
YEAH, HE HOSTS
DATING EVENTS WORLDWIDE.

33:38.233 --> 33:40.322
NEVER STAYS IN ONE PLACE
FOR MORE THAN A YEAR.

33:40.409 --> 33:42.759
ALWAYS CHANGES THE NAME AND
CHARITY OF HIS LATEST AUCTION.

33:42.846 --> 33:44.152
THAT'S A GREAT SETUP.

33:44.239 --> 33:46.459
HE PUTS ON THESE AUCTIONS,
LINES UP THE SUITORS...

33:46.546 --> 33:47.460
SHE KNOCKS THEM DOWN.

33:47.547 --> 33:48.852
WE NEED A CONCRETE LINK

33:48.939 --> 33:50.724
BETWEEN THESE TWO
AND THE CHARITIES.

33:50.811 --> 33:52.247
I'LL TALK TO HIM.

33:52.334 --> 33:53.335
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA SAY?

33:53.422 --> 33:54.858
THAT MY DATE
DIDN'T WORK OUT.

33:54.945 --> 33:57.600
SHE WAS A NICE GIRL
WHO PREFERS...NICE GIRLS.

33:57.687 --> 34:00.255
I WAS GONNA SAY "BLONDES,"
BUT WE CAN RUN WITH THAT, TOO.

34:00.342 --> 34:02.170
SHOULD GIVE US ENOUGH TIME
TO CASE THE OFFICE.

34:02.257 --> 34:03.041
WHO IS "US"?

34:03.128 --> 34:05.304
WHY'D I ASK?

34:05.391 --> 34:07.567
ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE LOOKING FOR SAFES,

34:07.654 --> 34:10.222
VAULTS, AND LOCKED CABINETS --
KEEP AN EYE OUT.

34:10.309 --> 34:12.224
HEY, HEY.
GREAT TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

34:12.311 --> 34:15.227
AH, YES, MR. MUNROE.
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

34:15.314 --> 34:17.316
WELL, I WAS JUST WONDERING
ABOUT YOUR NEXT EVENT.

34:17.403 --> 34:19.840
AH.

34:19.927 --> 34:23.365
I TAKE IT...
THINGS DIDN'T WORK OUT.

34:23.452 --> 34:25.324
WELL, YOU KNOW, SOME GUYS
PROPOSE ON THE FIRST DATE.

34:25.411 --> 34:26.629
SOME DON'T MAKE IT
TO THE SECOND.

34:26.716 --> 34:28.544
I SEE.

34:28.631 --> 34:31.069
AND WITH REGARDS TO YOUR
LITTLE FRIEND OVER THERE,

34:31.156 --> 34:32.896
WE HAVE A --

34:32.983 --> 34:35.290
A CERTAIN
HEIGHT REQUIREMENT.

34:35.377 --> 34:36.683
OH, NO, NO.
HE'S, UH --

34:36.770 --> 34:38.163
HE'S ALL SET
WITH THE LADIES.

34:38.250 --> 34:39.555
REALLY?
OH, YEAH.

34:39.642 --> 34:41.949
WELL, I'M SORRY TO SAY
MY NEXT EVENT

34:42.036 --> 34:44.604
WON'T BE FOR TWO MONTHS,
AND THAT'S IN FLORIDA.

34:44.691 --> 34:46.171
I LOVE THE SUNSHINE STATE.

34:46.258 --> 34:48.303
AM I STILL TALL ENOUGH TO FILL
OUT AN APPLICATION, OR...?

34:48.390 --> 34:49.783
[ Chuckling ]
YES, OF COURSE.

34:49.870 --> 34:51.045
I'LL GO GET IT
FROM THE BACK.

34:51.132 --> 34:53.178
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:57.530 --> 34:59.227
8414.

34:59.314 --> 35:01.186
STANDARD BANKS-SMITH
SECURITY SYSTEM,

35:01.273 --> 35:03.710
BUT IT'S GONNA BE HARD
TO GET IN HERE WITH
HIM HANGING AROUND.

35:03.797 --> 35:05.146
THEN WE WILL HAVE TO
GET TO IT LATER.

35:05.233 --> 35:06.321
AH.

35:06.408 --> 35:08.758
THERE YOU ARE.

35:08.845 --> 35:09.933
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

35:10.020 --> 35:10.934
ONE MORE THING.

35:11.021 --> 35:12.153
I LOVE THIS SPACE.

35:12.240 --> 35:13.459
DO -- DO YOU LOVE IT?

35:13.546 --> 35:15.504
YEAH.
HIGH CEILINGS!

35:15.591 --> 35:17.332
MM.
DO YOU RENT IT OUT?

35:17.419 --> 35:19.334
YES, IT IS POSSIBLE.

35:19.421 --> 35:20.814
MY FRIEND, MR. WILLIAMS --

35:20.901 --> 35:23.121
UH, WE ATTENDED
YOUR LAST AUCTION TOGETHER --

35:23.208 --> 35:24.600
OF COURSE, YES.
HE'S OUR BIG WINNER.

35:24.687 --> 35:26.994
YES, HE HAD BETTER LUCK
THAN I DID.

35:27.081 --> 35:28.430
AND HE ASKED ME
TO HELP HIM

35:28.517 --> 35:30.998
WITH A...CERTAIN
CELEBRATION.

35:31.085 --> 35:32.739
[ TECHNO MUSIC PLAYS ]

35:38.658 --> 35:39.572
Neal: PETER!

35:39.659 --> 35:41.182
OH.

35:41.269 --> 35:42.618
WELCOME TO
YOUR BACHELOR PARTY!

35:42.705 --> 35:44.011
CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU DID THIS.

35:44.098 --> 35:44.925
OH, YOU'RE WELCOME.

35:45.012 --> 35:46.753
NOT WHAT I MEANT.
COME ON.

35:46.840 --> 35:49.973
NOW WE HAVE THE ENTIRE NIGHT
TO GET INTO JAMESON'S OFFICE.

35:50.060 --> 35:52.454
THE HARVARD CREW IS ALL OVER
THE PLACE FOR BACKUP.

35:52.541 --> 35:53.673
THIS IS BUSINESS.

35:53.760 --> 35:55.414
IT IS NOT PLEASURE.

35:55.501 --> 35:57.764
WHAT IS HEDOING HERE?

35:57.851 --> 36:01.681
I LOVE
NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC.

36:01.768 --> 36:04.814
"THE MATING HABITS OF MIDLEVEL
GOVERNMENT EMPLOYEES" --

36:04.901 --> 36:06.338
TOTALLY CAPTIVATING.

36:06.425 --> 36:08.383
WELL, I'M NOT ON DUTY.
I'M GOING TO GET A DRINK.

36:14.128 --> 36:15.564
THIS ANYTHING LIKE
YOUR FIRST ONE?

36:15.651 --> 36:16.609
NO.
WOW.

36:18.350 --> 36:20.395
PETER.
HMM.

36:22.484 --> 36:24.791
ALL RIGHT,
I'LL DISTRACT.

36:24.878 --> 36:25.792
YOU GET
IN THE RECORDS ROOM.

36:51.557 --> 36:53.385
GOT ANYTHING?

36:53.472 --> 36:54.821
NO.

36:58.651 --> 36:59.434
I'M GONNA GET A DRINK.

37:01.915 --> 37:03.482
NOTHING.

37:03.569 --> 37:04.700
GREAT.

37:04.787 --> 37:06.311
I DON'T KNOW
WHO'S GONNA KILL ME FIRST --

37:06.398 --> 37:07.834
MY WIFE OR MY FIANCéE.

37:07.921 --> 37:10.358
WHAT IF I TOLD YOU THERE'S A WAY
TO SPOOK YOUR LADY

37:10.445 --> 37:12.273
INTO LEADING US
STRAIGHT TO THE MONEY?

37:12.360 --> 37:14.319
HOW?
USE WHAT WE GOT.

37:14.406 --> 37:17.235
NEAL, WHAT WE'VE GOT
ARE STROBE LIGHTS, PROBIES,

37:17.322 --> 37:18.801
WOMEN, AND BOOZE.

37:18.888 --> 37:19.976
EXACTLY.

37:20.063 --> 37:21.151
HAVE A PROBIE
GRAB A CAMERA

37:21.239 --> 37:22.283
FROM THE
SURVEILLANCE TRUCK.

37:22.370 --> 37:23.893
WE'RE TAKING SHOTS.

37:23.980 --> 37:25.068
MR. JAMESON!

37:25.155 --> 37:26.461
COME ON,
JOIN US FOR A DRINK.

37:26.548 --> 37:28.855
OH, NO. NO, I REALLY NEED
TO KEEP AN EYE ON THE SPACE.

37:28.942 --> 37:29.943
OH, COME ON.
I OWE YOU ONE.

37:30.030 --> 37:31.466
WEOWE YOU ONE.

37:31.553 --> 37:34.252
YES, NONE OF US WOULD BE HERE
IF IT WASN'T FOR YOU.

37:34.339 --> 37:35.688
WELL,
IF YOU PUT IT THAT WAY,

37:35.775 --> 37:37.211
I GUESS ONE LITTLE DRINK
WOULDN'T HURT.

37:37.298 --> 37:38.212
ALL RIGHT.

37:38.299 --> 37:40.301
GENTLEMEN, CHEERS.

37:40.388 --> 37:41.563
CHEERS.CHEERS.

37:41.650 --> 37:43.435
CONGRATULATIONS.

37:43.522 --> 37:45.393
MMM!

37:45.480 --> 37:46.960
AAH! THAT BURNS!

37:47.047 --> 37:48.831
DELICIOUS. THANK YOU.
YOU GUYS HAVE FUN.

37:48.918 --> 37:50.006
Neal: NO, NO, NO, NO.
HOLD ON.

37:50.093 --> 37:52.400
BARTENDER,
ANOTHER ROUND?

37:52.487 --> 37:54.184
NO, NO. NO, REALLY.COME ON. I DISAGREE.

37:54.272 --> 37:56.274
THIS IS MY BEST FRIEND'S
BACHELOR PARTY.

37:56.361 --> 37:58.363
LET'S MAKE IT...

37:58.450 --> 37:59.407
A NIGHT TO REMEMBER.

37:59.494 --> 38:00.365
MM-HMM!

38:00.452 --> 38:02.018
CONGRATS.
THANKS.

38:02.105 --> 38:03.977
HAVE A WONDERFUL LIFE.

38:04.064 --> 38:05.239
MMM.

38:05.326 --> 38:06.414
OKAY! OH, GOD!

38:06.501 --> 38:07.850
YEAH,
THAT'S DELICIOUS.

38:07.937 --> 38:09.765
YEAH, IT IS.ONE MORE.
NO, TOP SHELF.

38:09.852 --> 38:11.245
AND CHEERS AGAIN.AND CHEERS AGAIN.

38:11.332 --> 38:13.203
AAH! HA!

38:13.291 --> 38:15.597
YOU KNOW, IT DOES GO DOWN EASY.
FOUR, FIVE, SIX TIMES...

38:15.684 --> 38:16.990
YOU CAN BARELY TASTE IT.

38:17.077 --> 38:18.687
YOU BEAT US ON THAT ONE!

38:18.774 --> 38:19.862
MUCH HAPPINESS.

38:19.949 --> 38:21.864
CHEERS.
CHEERS.

38:21.951 --> 38:22.909
THANK YOU.

38:26.216 --> 38:28.828
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

38:28.915 --> 38:30.264
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

38:30.351 --> 38:32.092
MISS THOMAS? WHAT CAN YOU
TELL ME ABOUT THIS MAN?

38:32.179 --> 38:33.746
YOU'RE FBI?

38:33.833 --> 38:36.139
I WAS UNDERCOVER AT
MR. JAMESON'S LAST FUNDRAISER.

38:36.226 --> 38:38.054
WE BELIEVE HE HAD
ILLICIT FINANCIAL DEALINGS

38:38.141 --> 38:39.099
PRIOR TO HIS DEATH.

38:39.186 --> 38:40.143
HIS DEATH?

38:40.230 --> 38:41.406
WHAT HAPPENED?

38:41.493 --> 38:43.103
WE'RE WAITING
ON THE TOXICOLOGY REPORT.

38:43.190 --> 38:45.279
I'M HERE BECAUSE I NEED
TO QUESTION EVERYONE

38:45.366 --> 38:47.542
AFFILIATED WITH THE
SOCIETY HOUSE'S RECENT AUCTION.

38:47.629 --> 38:50.763
I'M SORRY. UM...

38:50.850 --> 38:53.113
THIS IS A SHOCK,
BUT I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

38:55.420 --> 38:56.899
LOOKS LIKE DIANA GOT TO HER.

38:56.986 --> 38:58.248
SHE'S HEADING
TOWARDS THE BANK.

38:58.336 --> 38:59.989
SHE'LL BE CLEARING OUT THE MONEY
ANY MINUTE NOW.

39:00.076 --> 39:03.384
GOOD. GIVE JAMESON
HIS WAKE-UP CALL.

39:03.471 --> 39:05.430
[ Dialing ]

39:05.517 --> 39:08.128
[ RINGTONE PLAYS
"SHAVE AND A HAIRCUT" ]

39:18.138 --> 39:19.618
[ BEEPS ]

39:33.196 --> 39:35.808
PETER,
YOU'RE ON STANDBY.

39:40.769 --> 39:42.162
HEY!

39:42.249 --> 39:43.511
I GOT A PING
FROM THE BANK.

39:43.598 --> 39:44.947
WHY DID YOU DRAIN
OUR ACCOUNT?

39:45.034 --> 39:46.732
WAIT A MINUTE.
THEY TOLD ME YOU WERE DEAD.

39:46.819 --> 39:48.037
WHAT?
WHO TOLD YOU I WAS DEAD?

39:48.124 --> 39:49.256
Peter: WE DID.

39:49.343 --> 39:51.519
WAIT A MINUTE.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

39:51.606 --> 39:53.086
YOU TWO
ARE UNDER ARREST.

39:53.173 --> 39:54.696
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU'RE FBI, TOO?

39:54.783 --> 39:57.220
YEAH, LET'S JUST SAY
I'M THE ADVENTUROUS TYPE.

39:57.307 --> 39:58.396
Neal:
UH, SPEAKING OF,

39:58.483 --> 39:59.614
I THINK WE WERE ALL

39:59.701 --> 40:01.224
A LITTLE ADVENTUROUS
LAST NIGHT.

40:01.311 --> 40:02.922
FURTHER
INCRIMINATING EVIDENCE.

40:03.009 --> 40:04.402
SHOULD WE GIVE HIM
A LITTLE SLIDE SHOW HERE?

40:04.489 --> 40:05.359
Peter:
YEAH. YEAH.

40:05.446 --> 40:07.100
HERE'S YOU
ON SHOT NUMBER EIGHT,

40:07.187 --> 40:09.058
HAVING A GOOD TIME.

40:09.145 --> 40:12.148
HERE'S YOU ON SHOT NUMBER 12
HAVING A GREAT TIME.

40:12.235 --> 40:15.064
THIS IS WHEN YOU TOLD US
YOU HAD A BIG PAYDAY COMING UP.

40:15.151 --> 40:16.718
GREAT. GOOD JOB.

40:16.805 --> 40:18.285
AND THAT'S WHEN
YOU TOLD ME

40:18.372 --> 40:20.679
I SHOULD ENJOY
THE HONEYMOON PHASE WHILE I CAN.

40:20.766 --> 40:22.985
OH, HERE'S WHERE YOU SAID
YOU WERE TIRED

40:23.072 --> 40:24.726
AND WANTED TO GO TO BED.

40:24.813 --> 40:28.034
Neal:
SOMETHING ABOUT HAVING TO TIE UP
LOOSE ENDS IN THE MORNING.

40:28.121 --> 40:29.775
THEY SAY THAT ALCOHOL'S
A TRUTH SERUM FOR SOME PEOPLE.

40:29.862 --> 40:31.733
YOU ARE DEFINITELY ONE OF THEM,
MY FRIEND.

40:31.820 --> 40:34.910
AND, IN CASE YOU WERE WONDERING,
WE GOT IT ALL ON TAPE.

40:36.651 --> 40:38.436
PETER.
HMM.

40:38.523 --> 40:40.699
I ACTUALLY THOUGHT
WE HAD SOMETHING.

40:40.786 --> 40:42.440
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT WASN'T REAL.

40:42.527 --> 40:43.484
NOT EVEN OUR TANGO?

40:43.571 --> 40:45.486
OH.
MM.

40:45.573 --> 40:48.184
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY
THAT BREAKING UP IS TOUGH.

40:48.271 --> 40:50.709
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
IT WASN'T ME.

40:50.796 --> 40:51.753
IT WAS YOU.

40:51.840 --> 40:54.016
PETER...

40:57.019 --> 40:59.282
THAT'S A SHAME.

40:59.369 --> 41:00.283
WOULD HAVE BEEN
A NICE WEDDING.

41:00.370 --> 41:02.416
YEAH.

41:02.503 --> 41:04.157
ELIZABETH ORDERED MOST
OF THE ARRANGEMENTS ALREADY.

41:04.244 --> 41:05.593
I'M SURE SHE DID
A GREAT JOB.

41:05.680 --> 41:07.029
IT'S TOO BAD WE'LL HAVE TO
SHIP THEM ALL BACK.

41:07.116 --> 41:11.120
OR SHIP THEM
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

41:11.207 --> 41:12.470
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

41:14.254 --> 41:16.082
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

41:16.169 --> 41:17.910
PETER NEEDS
YOUR HELP RIGHT AWAY.

41:17.997 --> 41:19.738
OKAY.

41:26.222 --> 41:28.311
HONEY?

41:28.398 --> 41:31.010
HEY, BEAUTIFUL.

41:31.097 --> 41:32.490
WHAT IS THIS?

41:32.577 --> 41:35.754
I'M SORRY FOR WHAT YOU
WENT THROUGH ON THIS ONE.

41:35.841 --> 41:37.930
SO, TO MAKE IT UP TO YOU,

41:38.017 --> 41:41.411
I'M GIVING YOU THE WEDDING
YOU ALWAYS WANTED.

41:41.499 --> 41:44.632
SMALL, SIMPLE.

41:44.719 --> 41:45.720
JUST US.

41:51.987 --> 41:55.469
WILL YOU MARRY ME AGAIN?

41:56.818 --> 41:58.298
YES.

41:58.385 --> 42:00.692
AS MANY TIMES
AS YOU ASK.

42:00.779 --> 42:02.737
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

42:10.919 --> 42:12.138
PREACHER'S HERE.

42:12.225 --> 42:13.487
THAT WAS FAST.

42:13.574 --> 42:15.010
SORRY I'M LATE.

42:15.097 --> 42:16.882
DON'T TELL ME
HE'S BEEN ORDAINED.

42:16.969 --> 42:18.187
TWICE.
TAX DODGE?

42:18.274 --> 42:19.841
OH, YEAH,
LIKE I PAY TAXES.

42:19.928 --> 42:20.973
WILL YOU BEAR WITNESS?

42:21.060 --> 42:22.496
OF COURSE.

42:24.150 --> 42:26.674
DEARLY BELOVED,
WE ARE GATHERED HERE TODAY

42:26.761 --> 42:30.286
TO CELEBRATE THE UNION
OF...SUIT

42:30.373 --> 42:34.508
AND MRS. SUIT ONCE AGAIN.
